h3. Problem Definition

Currently, the user receiving daily email update reports at a random time and there is no option to schedule a time when daily email update reports can be send

h3. Issue Summary

When using the Filter Results macro and accessing Fields to Display, it is not possible to add a text custom field to the list.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a Text custom field on JIRA, selecting the Number one;
 # Still on JIRA, create a filter from a project that you added the previously created custom field;
 # Go to Confluence and create a new page;
 # Call the widget with */filter*;
 # Chose the filter you just created;
 # On the add fields drop-down list, find the text custom field you created and try to add it;

h3. Expected Results

The text field should be added to the list of fields to display.
h3. Actual Results

The field never shows up in the list after pressing *Add*
h3. Workaround

Users may use the Jira issue macro to display the field.

This request is for Confluence to allow apps to provide dynamic content macro editing inline with the Confluence editor.

Dynamic content macros can contribute custom editors by specifying an editor field with appropriate sub-fields such as "url" to identify the resource providing the editor. When editing a page containing a dynamic content macro with a custom editor, a web panel displays the dynamic content macro in "view mode" instead of "edit mode". The user must click the pencil icon to open a dialog to see the dynamic content macro in edit mode.

An `\{output.type}` context parameter can be specified in the macro's view resource URL so conceivably the app could provide an edit version of the macro if it detects the output type is `preview`, however, Confluence places a mask over the macro to prevent interaction. 

An aggressive solution would involve always displaying the macro's editor in the Confluence editor, but a more conservative approach would allow apps to opt-in to inline editing by supplying a new field within the custom `editor` section. For example:
{code:java}
{
  "url": "/my-view-resource",
  ...
  "editor": {
    "url": "/my-editor-resource",
    "inlineEditing": true,
    ...
  }
}{code}

h3. Issue Summary
Content of a custom *label* field is not showing in the "Jira issue/filter" macro 

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a Jira project;
# Create a custom *label* field;
# Add information in this custom field;
# Create a Confluence page;
# Add the "Jira issue/filter" macro in this page;
# Create a query to search project where you added information to the custom *label* field created;
# Open the *Display options* of the macro
# Add the custom *label* field created in the *Columns to display*

h3. Expected Results
The macro will show the columns set in the search of your macro, and the proper information of those fields.

h3. Actual Results
The custom *label* field is not populated.

h3. Workaround
There is no workaround at the moment.
